es, but IMV most of the things people who are unfamiliar with home education worry about, are, in practice, not founded. &#10;Certainly the theme of this article is about trying to convince people to follow up the concerns that pop up for them, rather than assume that something they are not familiar with is weird and therefore most likely dangerous. &#10;The danger for Khyra Ishaq had nothing to do with her education and everything to do with poor social services performance - yet it appears that it is convenient for various interested parties to point at home education. Social services people detract from their failings by blaming the home education officer - whose job has no welfare remit beyond reporting concerns to SS - and those who are anti home education, can point to Khyra Ishaq and claim HE must need more regulation - despite Khyra's death having nothing to do with her place of education. Scapegoats, red herrings, whatever you may call them - but whatever concerns you may have about home education will not justify any registration and monitoring scheme or any imposed curriculum. &#10;Despite feeling it is not pertinent to the article, I am sure that if you post those many potential problems/issues you envisage with home education, that posters here would be happy to address them. &#10;best wishes"/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1609" language="en" documentId="1162" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Baldtwitlion" date="29 July 2010 8:53pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6892014" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="7" thumbsDown="0" origId="1162" notes="" title="Home education: precious, not dangerous"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="5"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="6" end="260"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="261" end="420"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="421" end="647"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="648" end="1396"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="1397" end="1597"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="1598" end="1609"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59 63"/></xmi:XMI>